name: 1.4.9-alpha01
body: Updated Kotlin and KSP to 1.7.0
Update Kotlin to 1.6.20

name: 1.4.8-alpha02
body: Swapped out kotlin-compiler pre-release dependencies that are no longer available

name: 1.4.8-alpha01
body: - Update KSP to 1.6.20-M1-1.0.2
- Update to Kotlin 1.6.10 and KSP 1.0.2

- Upragded Kotlin to 1.6.0 and various other dependency upgrades
- The KSP integration now has a `allWarningsAsErrors` option
- All classpaths used in the compilation are now added to the result classloader automatically, so that all classes used by the compiled classes can be loaded
- There is a new method `KotlinCompilation.addPreviousResultToClasspath` for including previous results when chaining multiple `KotlinCompilation`s

- dependency upgrades
- new properties for compiler options
- update Kotlin and KSP to 1.5.31

- Update Kotlin and KSP to 1.5.30
- JDK 16 compatibility

- Updated Kotlin and KSP versions
- Updated other dependencies
- Updated kotlin-compiler-embeddable and KSP to 1.5.10

- Updated kotlin-compiler-embeddable and KSP to 1.5.0
- Fixed a bug where KSP (and other compiler plugins) would not be executed when only Java source files are given
- kotlin-compiler-embeddable has become an `api` dependency
- Various other dependency updates

- Various dependency upgrades
- Note: Breaking change in the API of the transitive dependency on KSP lead to a breaking change for users of kotlin-compile-tesing-ksp
- New property for enabling the old JVM backend of kotlinc

- Various dependency upgrades, most notably KSP
- Significant performance improvements thanks to @yigit

- Change name of resources directory to follow conventions KSP #97
- Fix Java sources not reported to KSP #103 
- Various dependency upgrades
- Fixed KSP logs not being captured

- Updated KSP
- Allow passing args to KSP

- Update dependencies
- Fix jitback build
- Fix NoSuchMethodError

- Updated Kotlin to 1.4.0
- Moved KSP to regular submodule
- Better automation of release process

- More robust parsing of the Javac version string
- Release KSP support
- Update bundled compiler to 1.3.72
- Updated bundled compiler to 1.3.70

- It's now possible to add `CommandLineProcessor`s to the compilation directly to be able to test compiler plugins that take arguments

- Improved regex parsing of Kotlin compiler version strings

- Updated bundled compiler to 1.3.61
- Updated bundled compiler to 1.3.60

- Compiler plugins can now be added either as instances or via the `pluginClasspath`
- Source files generated by kapt are now in the list of generated files,
- Easier filtering of generated files

- Check file extensions automatically when creating `SourceFile`s with the new factory functions
- Less noisy output/verbose flag actually works as intended

- Nicer SourceFile factory functions for better IDE support
- Fix kapt pluginClasspath when other ComponentRegistrars are on the classpath
- Fix SourceFile.fromPath compilation

- Updated bundled compiler version to 1.3.41
- Discover JDK and tools.jar automatically by default
- Verbose output by default
- Fix parsing of resources path on Linux and MacOS
- Fix parsing of javac version string on version 12
- Removed ScriptUtils
